The paper deals with constraint propagation algorithms for regular counting constraints, which are commonly used in sequencing and timetabling problems. This makes cs.CP (Computation and Language) the most likely category, as it deals with constraint satisfaction problems. The use of deterministic finite automata (DFA) and their extensions also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category. The paper also mentions the use of polynomial time algorithms, which is a common topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with regular languages, which is a topic in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the paper mentions the relationship between regular counting constraints and the CostRegular constraint, which is a topic in cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
